language-name: The name of a language in its native script
language-name-romanized: For non-latin scripts, The Romanized version of a language name.
language-name-romanized-sorted: The romanized version of a language name, sorted in alphabetical, left-to-right order, without diacritics. For example, romanized Arabic is 'Arabiyah, Al' whereas the sorted romanized version is  'Al-ʿArabīyah'

wiki.name: Label for Wikipedia
wiki.entries: The name of a content page on Wikipedia, pluralized. For example, in english: articles.
